expert_edge@delphi.com (Bob Felton) writes:
: I am a civil engineer who has had a "hobby" interest in cryptography for
: a long time, and so I've been following this newsgroup for a while.  A
: constant theme seems to be ... where can I find books, get info?  It has
: me wondering if a mail-order bookstore dedicated to books and software in
: the crypto area might be a success.  I'd much appreciate knowing if any
: regular participants in this newsgroup would be interested in such a
: service.
: 		Thanks,
: 		Bob Felton


	Concerning mail-order books on cryptography, the
following was taken from a repost in this newsgroup about
a year or so ago:

>
>
>
>               Aegean Park Press
>               P.O. Box 2837
>               Laguna Hills, CA 92654-0387
>               (714) 586-8811
>
> Wayne Barker, who runs it is very nice (and talkative).  When I was in
> Mission Viejo (the next town to Laguna Hills) visiting my mother, I
> gave him a call and he invited me over: it's run out of his house.  He
> worked for many years in Military Intelligence and has lots of
> fascinating stories to tell.
>

I've been receiving their catalog for over 2 years now and the stuff
you can find there is very, very good.  The books are a bit expensive,
though.  A lot of the books can be found nowhere else.  Highly
recommended.


	Joe	pjhong@clio.rad.sunysb.edu
